Question

According to the US National Comorbidity Survey (1995), what is the lifetime prevalence of at least one other psychiatric disorder in those suffering from PTSD?

 
 
 
 

Answer: c) 83%

 

Rationale:

The National Comorbidity Survey, a large epidemiological study of the prevalence of mental disorders in the US general population, examined comorbidity of PTSD with other lifetime psychiatric diagnoses. It found that PTSD is a highly comorbid condition, with a lifetime history of at least one other disorder in 88% of men and 79% of women who suffer from PTSD.
